    "name": "Mesh convergence study for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was performed on the 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, very fine) were evaluated by monitoring construct stiffness and von Mises stress distributions at the screw-rod junction. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). Results indicated that the medium mesh achieved a GCI below 1% for stiffness QoI, confirming mesh-independent behavior. The study was executed in Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 under the same boundary conditions as the validation simulations.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
