      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical implementation verified against benchmark problems with known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "The FEA solver was verified against NAFEMS benchmark problems for beam bending and contact mechanics. Results matched analytical solutions within 0.5%. Additional patch tests confirmed element formulation correctness for the hexahedral and tetrahedral elements used in the pedicle screw model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence demonstrated via GCI < 2% for all QoIs of interest; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "The mesh convergence study (Activity: mesh-convergence-study-v1) demonstrated GCI < 1% for construct stiffness at the medium mesh density. Four refinement levels were evaluated. Richardson extrapolation confirmed asymptotic convergence. The medium mesh was selected for all validation simulations. Discretization error is bounded and acceptable."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence criteria documented; residuals monitored and within acceptable tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver with force and displacement convergence criteria of 0.1% and 0.5% respectively. Residual histories reviewed for all 11 simulation cases; no convergence failures observed. Solver error contribution estimated as negligible relative to other uncertainty sources."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified analyst; boundary conditions and material assignments independently verified.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of model setup conducted by a senior FEA analyst not involved in the original model construction. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material property assignments verified against the ASTM F1717 test specification and physical test setup photographs. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified relative to the COU physics; nonlinear material behavior and large-deformation effects included where relevant.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model adopted for titanium alloy components; justified by the fact that yield force is a QoI and plasticity onset is the endpoint rather than post-yield behavior. Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM) enabled. Frictional contact at screw-rod interface modeled with coefficient of friction 0.2, consistent with literature values for Ti-Ti interfaces."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measured values with documented uncertainty; sensitivity analysis performed for key inputs.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E = 114 GPa, ν = 0.34 for Ti-6Al-4V) sourced from ASTM B265 certified material test reports for the actual device lot. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of representative screws (n=3). One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis showed stiffness QoI sensitivity to elastic modulus of 0.95 (near-linear) and to friction coefficient of 0.08 (low sensitivity)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production devices; traceability to lot and manufacturing records documented; sufficient sample size for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; all from production lots with full traceability. Constructs assembled per ASTM F1717 with UHMWPE blocks. Sample size sufficient for mean and standard deviation estimation; power analysis confirmed 80% power to detect 10% QoI difference at α=0.05."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the COU; multiple test configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. No torsion, tension, or fatigue conditions included in this validation package. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3) due to the single test condition; this shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given the primary regulatory submission focus on static compression-bending performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs shown to be equivalent to physical test inputs within documented tolerances; discrepancies quantified and their impact on QoI assessed.",
      "rationale": "FEA model geometry matched to physical test specimens via CMM data. Material properties matched to certified test reports. UHMWPE block stiffness characterized experimentally and input to FEA. Rod pre-torque replicated in FEA via pretension elements. Residual input discrepancies quantified; maximum impact on stiffness QoI estimated at 1.2%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined a priori; validation uncertainty (uval) computed; E/uval ratio evaluated against acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Acceptance bounds defined a priori: <10% mean absolute percentage error and E/uval < 1.96. Validation uncertainty uval computed from experimental variability (n=11) and model input uncertainty. E/uval = 1.31 for stiffness, 1.54 for yield force, 1.42 for force at 40 mm. All metrics within acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory acceptance criteria; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs selected: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. These are the primary ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics and directly relate to the clinical failure mode of screw-rod construct fracture during spinal fusion. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical affairs team."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities replicate the COU loading, geometry, and boundary conditions to a degree commensurate with the model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 COU: identical screw geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), identical loading configuration (compression-bending), identical UHMWPE block material and dimensions, and testing across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability. Validation activities are highly relevant to the COU."
    }
